categories, from the principle of apperception. Schulting challenges this standard view and aims to resuscitate the main motivation behind Reich's project. He argues, in agreement with Reich's main thesis about the derivability of the functions of judgement, that Kant indeed does mean to derive, in full a priori fashion, the categories from the principle of apperception. Schulting also shows that, given the general assumptions of the Critical philosophy, Kant's derivation is successful and that absent an account of the derivation of the categories from apperception, the B-Deduction cannot really be understood. New edition. First published 2012 as "Kant's Deduction and Apperception. Explaining the Categories" (Palgrave Macmillan)   aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 23. Nov 2018) 4aCategories. 4aErkenntnistheorie. 4aKant, Immanuel. 4aKategorientafel. 4aepistemology.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE  DG 2019 Englishz978311061685908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2018 Englishz978311060425208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2018z9783110603255oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Philosophy 2018 Englishz978311060421408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Philosophy 2018z9783110603217oZDB-23-DPH0 cEPUBz97831105828710 cprintz978311058269740uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9783110584301423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9783110584301.jpg  a978-3-11-060421-4  EBOOK PACKAGE Philosophy 2018 Englishb2018  a978-3-11-060425-2  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2018 Englishb2018  a978-3-11-061685-9  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE  DG 2019 English  aEBA_CL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_SSHAL